'''Ivan Cherednik''' (Иван Владимирович Чередник) is a Russian [[mathematician]].   He introduced [[Cherednik algebra|double affine Hecke algebras]], and used them to prove [[Macdonald's constant term conjecture]] in {{harv|Cherednik|1995}}. He has also dealt with [[algebraic geometry]], [[number theory]] and [[Soliton|Soliton equations]]. His research interests include [[representation theory]], [[mathematical physics]], and [[algebraic combinatorics]]. He is currently a professor of mathematics at the [[University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill]], specializing in [[combinatorics]].

